<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{6}{y}={48}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{6}{y}={69}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},-{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --9. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{9}}{{-{{4}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{9}}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left(-{4}{x}+-{6}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{9}}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left({48}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{9}\right)}{x}+{13.5}{y}=-{108}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{6}{y}={69}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{19.5}{y}=-{39}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{39}}{{19.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{6}{\left(-{2}\right)}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left({12}\right)}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={48}-{\left({12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{36}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},-{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

